2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the behavior of networked agents exchanging evidence, which can be seen as a control problem in systems and control. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with the consensus among agents in a network, which is a key topic in multiagent systems. 
4. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the framework of Dempster-Shafer theory, which is a probabilistic reasoning framework used in software engineering. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper utilizes results from matrix theory and graph theory, which are key topics in information theory.
